	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145143><span id=Scholar>wolas</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>28 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.19]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hehe sorry for the reaction but i see so many twink 50+ bards that dont even know how to CC in dungeons... or just sing 1 or 2 song at a time and most often the wrong ones.<br><br>Bard is a really hard (but fun) class to play and needs some practice.<br><br>So with in mind an amount of 10 20 k i would say:<br><br>- a good drum (walrus skin 1kp or drum of march 4kp). This will help a lot (faster selo is always nice) Anyway drum of the march is only a slight increase to walrus.<br>- For armor (hands, legs, arms, boots, head) you could grab some pieces of Singing steel (600pp to 1kp) or Crystal chitin 2kp (depending on what is available in bazaar). Singing steel has slightly better ac and some rather useless effects but no stats. 5kp to fill the 5 slots<br>- For chest a Barbed Ringmail is just fine. 4kp<br>- Cougar claw earings and 6ac 65 hp rings les than 1kp for all set<br>- some cha jewellry<br>- bracer of scaveging for dex and sta 300pp<br>- hero bracer 500pp<br>- crested spauldron for sta 200pp<br>- spider fur collar, cloak and belt 1.5 kp for all<br>- face : worked dragonskin mask good ac and cha<br>- Weapons: a pair of centi (LS and SS) but they tend to drain stamina a bit. Pick a Breath of Harmony if you find one to replace the centi SS. Its a good weapon and effect at 45 is nice. Rather rare so grab one if you can.<br><br>You ll be set for a long time.<br><br>Depending on choice and the economy of your server you should average between 10/20k (price given for AB server)<br><br>And if you have some more money a Singing Steel Breastplate is a must. (I wish my guild was strong enough to kill trakanon...)<br><br>Enjoy your bard.<br><br></p>&n